text: Elliniko or Ellinikon (, "Hellenic, Greek") may refer to several places in Greece: *Elliniko, a suburban city in southcentral Athens, the site of: ** the Ellinikon International Airport ** the Hellinikon Olympic Complex * , a village in Farres municipal unit * In Arcadia : ** Elliniko, Arcadia, a village in Gortynia municipality ** , a seaside village in Tyros municipal unit * , a village in Argos municipal unit *Elliniko, Chania, a village in Platanias municipal unit *Elliniko, Corinthia, a village in Evrostina municipal unit *Elliniko, Ioannina, a village in Katsanochoria *Elliniko, Kilkis, a village in Kroussa *Elliniko, Laconia, a village in Monemvasia municipal unit ==Related== * Aglianico or Ellenico, an Italian grape of Greek origin *Ellinika, Aetolia-Acarnania, a village in Aetolia-Acarnania *Ellinika, Euboea, a village in the northern part of Euboea
title: Elliniko (disambiguation)
